commitResults.messageBody: This reverts commit 81764c987c1d73a3c3bf7c30f1aa1cb13b183a4e.

Reformatted the Ui class to adhere to java coding standards.
Customised the replies given by the bot.

Reformat the printListFind(keyword) function to better adhere to the
coding standards. Added some custom log messages to better showcase
the functionality of the printListFind(keyword) method

Upon creating the proper dirs and files for the save file, added a new
log message to indicate if that action took place.
If there is already a save file -> Existing message
If there is no save file -> Creating dir message

Included JavaDocs for all the functions.
More inclusions of log messages such as when the file is corrupted.

JavaDocs for the latest Command (Find) is added to give better
understanding of the execute() function.
These docs will help to quickly identify the purpose of each function
when we need to edit or update them in the future.

Included JavaDocs to the constructor for Tobias and to all its
relevant functions. This will help to deduce quickly what each function
does in the future.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update existing classes and include javaFX
commitResults.messageBody:
By adding javaFX, removed the command line responses and replaced it
with Strings which is then printed onto the GUI of Tobias.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify code to adhere to code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
There were 2 instances of improper else-if code format that
deviates from standard code quality.

Clean up Tobias.java to remove unused function, run(), which was
initially used in the CLI interface
Modify code to adhere to code quality

These assertions check for the following :
- Task list is not empty or size is not negative
- Constants are not null (ie not altered)
Assertions to Ui class

Tag - Add tags to a task
Untag - Removes a tag from a task
Tagging is incorporated

By modifying the custom messages sent by the bot
we can make it sound more unique.

Moving forward, we can incorporate more custom commands
and custom replies.

With the inclusion of a ReplyCommand, one can add custom messages
to be replied to when a command is given.

This will help improve the quality of the bot's replies.

The TobiasException message will now reflect what the user
is able to ask the bot.

Tag, Untag and Reply Commands has Java Docs.

Java Docs makes it easier to explain the functionalities of
the Tag, Untag and Reply Commands.

Moving command guide from Parser to a Popup in the main window
makes it easier and clutter-free for user to view the user-guide.

Initially the parser had a very long if-else block with
all the conditions. By separating the conditions into a function
on its own, we can achieve better level-abstraction.

Initially, there was usage of wildcard imports in a few
of the classes. Rectifying it by only choosing what we need to
import.
